  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Rinse the cauliflower and remove the leaves.",
    "Cut the cauliflower into florets and place them in a bowl.",
    "Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with garlic, salt, and black pepper. Toss to coat.",
    "Spread the cauliflower on a baking sheet and roast for 20 minutes.",
    "While the cauliflower is roasting, melt the butter in a saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the chicken broth and bring to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and let the sauce simmer for 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in the queso fresco, cilantro, lime juice, chili flakes, and white pepper.",
    "Toss the roasted cauliflower with the sauce and top with crumbly cheese and breadcrumbs.",
    "Transfer the platter to a serving dish and drizzle with cheese sauce.",
    "Sprinkle with cayenne pepper, onion powder, and paprika.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
  ],
